Update hue logic

Adding new commands is more easier now.

Update README.md

removed all html tags using pure markdown, formatted to be markdownlint compliant as well

Edit wording and styling of README.md

- Reword dependencies sentence to improve clarity
- Bold `pip` to be consistent with `easy_install`
- Change `hue` from bold to code tags to disambiguate from `pip` and `easy_install`

Wrap long lines

This commit cleans up the README by wrapping long lines near the bottom
of the file. It also adds space to the comparison table to align the
cells nicely.

Simplify setup

This commit simplifies setup.py. Because `huepy/__init__.py` is a Python
file too, it can be imported in `setup.py`. This way we can use the
variables available in the init file. This makes determining the version
easier.  This commit does the same trick with `huepy/__init__.py` and
`huepy/hue.py`. It imports the hue source file, and generates a list for
all the created commands, no more hardcoding! :)

Port hue to Python3

This commit was necessary because support for Python2.* will drop after
2019. This commit addresses that problem by removing the unnecessary u''
from strings. The side effects are that it may not support Python
versions lower than 2.7 anymore.

Relevant issue: https://github.com/s0md3v/hue/issues/31

Fix hue import with python 3

During setup build with python3.8, the error No module named 'hue' appears.
This commit prevent this error to shows up.
